"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The function sns.set_context does not have an rc argument. The rc argument is used with sns.set_style to override the parameters that are part of the style definition. sns.set_context is used to set the plotting context parameters and does not accept an rc argument.\", \"patch\": \"8c8\\n< sns.set_context(rc=scale_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_context()\\n> sns.set_style(rc=scale_dict)\\n> sns.set_style(rc=style_dict) should be used after sns.set_context() to override the style parameters.\"}"